Moulting male; has RFF tag yellow from ~2001. Given new microchip. Recapture: no sign of burning; small patch of rubbed off hair at front of unit. Popular male with Seal Bay - Kangaroo Island staff - named "Big Ron"
Full grown male in good condition - moulting; had to pluck some hair to get access to patch of new hair on back.
Stopped emitting on the 22/11/2014 and the tag has not been retrieved
Good condition
Good condition

Good condition
Moderate condition - post moult
Really excellent condition - very fat for male at this stage (between breeding seasons) - called 'Chippy' by Seal Bay staff.
Good condition
Just sub- prime make in good condition

Good condition for animal just moulted. Almost fully moulted. Good on dart - but head-up and strong when mask applied and took some time to secure the mask, then went down good. On 5 for 5 then to 2, irregular shallow breaths initially but improved well with regular deep breaths after 3 min. Good gum colour and refill throughout.

Good condition. Just beginning to moult - was able to pull a patch of old hair out to access new grey coat. Only 3/4 of first dart injected, too much movement and power so needed a top-up. Hand injected 140 mg Zoletil at 1211. Head still up and eyes open after 10 minutes but easy mask. Kept on iso 5 for 5 min then turned down to 2 until end of procedure. Good regular breaths and excellent gum colour and refill throughout.
Excellent body cndition, almost completed its moult,  new microchip 982000063645079

Average condition - animal is just commencing moult so typical for post- breeding and pre- moult males looking a bit average. Commencing moulting - were able to pluck a nice clear patch and expose new coat for glueing. Great on dart - laid out, eyes shut head down, good breathing mask straight on. On 5 for 5, 3 for 5 then 2 until mask-off. Very regular breathing and great gum colour and excellent refill throughout.

Good condition. Moulting just commenced. Had to pluck a square of fur to stick tag to new coat. Lots of head shaking at 10 min and some mobility in flippers so hand injection of 120 mg Zoletil at 1042. Still head up and shaking head and eyes open on masking but managed to mask successfully. Maintained on ISO 5 for 5 min, then on 3 for 5 min and then 2 until end. Really good breathing, gum colour and refill throughout.
Good body condition, about 1/3 through moult. Has old flipper tag in RFF, probably from 2001, so 16 years old

Excellent condition - massive. Just finished moulting. Massive male was too frisky on dart 1, needed 2nd dart 1627 (170mg Zoletil), very upright with eyes open on mask, strong and fought it but masked ok. On iso 5 for 5 min then to 3 for 5 min then dropped to 2 until mask off. Good breathing, gum colour and refill throughout.
